    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-06-18T17:55:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-06-18T17:55:00-05:00" n="441"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d441">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">310.2/6–1853: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Mission at the United Nations</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d441fn1">Drafted by <persName>Gough</persName> and concurred
                        in by <persName corresp="#p_WAINHOUSEDW1">Wainhouse</persName>; cleared with
                        the Bureau of Far Eastern Affairs, the Bureau of European Affairs, and the
                        Executive Secretariat; approved for transmission and signed by <persName
                            corresp="#p_SANDIFERDV1">Sandifer</persName>; and repeated for action to
                        Canberra as telegram 213.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-06-18T18:55:00-04:00"
                            >June 18, 1953—6:55 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>500. Re hearings for representatives <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> and for
                    Chinese <gloss target="#t_Commies1">Commies</gloss> and North Koreans at resumed
                        <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss>. In your preparatory discussions other
                        <gloss target="#t_Del1">Del</gloss>s you should indicate our view as
                    follows:</p>
                <p>Since, apart from merely noting conclusion armistice, sole business before <gloss
                        target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> is to make appropriate arrangements for
                    participation <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> in Political Conference, it is
                    unnecessary and totally inappropriate for <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> hear
                    Chinese <gloss target="#t_Commies1">Commies</gloss> and North Koreans, and US
                    will vote against any proposal this effect. As victim aggression and as part of
                        <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> side resisting aggression, <gloss
                        target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> should properly be represented if it desires on
                    same basis as in previous <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> discussions Korean
                    case, i.e., <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> should be invited participate
                    without right vote.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DULLESJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
